    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Seiya Suzuki** (75.03) anchor the Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup as our most efficient starts. **Mickey Moniak** benefits from a massive +14% park factor boost and a favorable platoon setup against the opposing starter, while **Seiya Suzuki** receives a specialized efficiency bump thanks to the pitcher's slow delivery, which projects to enhance his stolen base opportunity\u2014a critical metric for our scarcity-weighted strategy. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (64.77) and **Corbin Carroll** (63.45) also provide high-upside production, with **Vinnie Pasquantino** leveraging a strong platoon advantage against a right-handed arm and **Corbin Carroll** overcoming the threat of an elite hold pitcher to remain a locked-in core play due to his high-leverage batting position.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Cole Young**, who fell just short of the 45-point threshold with a score of 42.74. While **Cole Young** possesses the speed profile we prioritize, his projection against a left-handed starter and a lackluster park factor made him less efficient than the remaining utility options. We are also monitoring the volatility surrounding **James Wood** (52.10); while his spot atop the order provides an excellent ceiling, the low xERA of the opposing pitcher indicates a tough path to production that requires a watchful eye. Caution is advised across the board regarding the base-stealing environment; while we have prioritized speed, **Dalton Rushing**, **Jose Caballero**, and **Corbin Carroll** are all facing pitchers with elite \"hold\" percentages, which may suppress our stolen base totals despite their solid projected output.",
